---
import SectionHeader from './SectionHeader.astro';
---

<section id="faq" class="py-24 border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <SectionHeader
        title="Frequently Asked Questions"
        subtitle="Everything you need to know about RNRepo."
        className="text-center"
      />
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            How do I verify that RNRepo is set up correctly?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          You can verify the setup by running a standard build and checking the
          Gradle logs. You should see RNRepo plugin tasks executing and
          replacing dependencies with artifacts from our maven repository.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            How do I opt out of RNRepo for specific libraries?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          You can exclude specific libraries in your build.gradle configuration
          block under the rnRepo settings.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            What happens if I have local patches for a library?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          RNRepo respects local patches if configured correctly. Typically, if
          patch-package detects changes, you might need to build that specific
          library from source.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            What if a library or React Native version isn't supported?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          You can request it! Or fall back to standard compilation for that
          specific library. The system is designed to mix and match.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            How can I see which libraries are pre-built?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          Check our libraries.json file in the GitHub repository or browse the
          packages index on our website.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            How do I request a new library to be added?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          Submit an issue or PR to the RNRepo GitHub repository with the library
          details.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            Is RNRepo secure? How can I verify artifacts?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          Security is a top priority. All builds run in isolated GitHub
          workflows that are fully transparentâ€”you can inspect any build's logs
          and source. Every artifact is GPG-signed, allowing you to verify
          authenticity. When downloading, you can trace any artifact back to its
          exact build workflow.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            Do library maintainers need to do anything?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          No, RNRepo works independently. However, maintainers are welcome to
          collaborate to ensure optimal build configurations.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20">
            Can you just pre-build everything?
          </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          Technically yes, but we focus on the most popular libraries to
          maximize impact and minimize maintenance overhead.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-item border-b border-rnrGrey-80">
        <summary class="faq-summary">
          <span class="font-medium text-rnrGrey-20"> Is iOS supported? </span>
          <svg
            class="faq-chevron w-5 h-5 text-rnrGrey-50"
            width="24"
            height="24"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          >
            <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline>
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <p
          class="faq-answer text-rnrGrey-40 text-sm leading-relaxed pr-8 pt-0 pb-4"
        >
          Currently, we focus on Android builds as they benefit most from
          pre-compilation. iOS support is being explored.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-item {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .faq-item summary {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-summary:hover span {
    color: #38acdd;
  }

  .faq-summary:hover .faq-chevron {
    color: #38acdd;
  }

  .faq-summary:focus {
    outline: none;
  }

  .faq-chevron {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition:
      transform 0.2s,
      color 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-item:global([open]) .faq-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    color: #38acdd;
  }

  .faq-answer {
    padding-top: 0;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    animation: fadeIn 0.3s ease-in-out;
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
    }
  }
</style>
